.TH wxActivateEvent 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxActivateEvent \- An activate event is sent when a window or application is being activated or deactivated.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
See: Overview events

.PP
This class is derived, and can use functions, from:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxEvent\fR

.RE

.PP
wxWidgets docs: wxActivateEvent

.SS "Events"

.PP
Use \fIwxEvtHandler:connect/3\fR with \fIwxActivateEventType\fR to subscribe to events of this type.

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxActivate() :: #wxActivate{}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxActivateEvent() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxActivateEventType() :: activate | activate_app | hibernate.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBgetActive(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxActivateEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the application or window is being activated, false otherwise.


.RE
